When considering a range of diverse animal species, a spectrum of sizes in the animal kingdom becomes apparent, varying greatly depending on the habitat and ecological niche. Listed from smallest to largest, the average lengths of animal specimens include:
- Fairyfly (0.2 mm / 0.008 in), a type of wasp and one of the smallest insects;
